In-Class Exercise 3: “Mickey”

Instructions
1. Create a folder in your class site / local git repository titled `mickey`
2. Create HTML and CSS files corresponding to the following code.

  `index.html`:
  

    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html>
    <head>
            <title>Mickey</title>
            <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/main.css" type="text/css" />
    </head>
    <body>
            <div id="canvas">
                    <div id="ear-1"></div>
                    <div id="ear-2"></div>
                    <div id="head"></div>
                    <div id="eye-1"></div>
                    <div id="eye-2"></div>
                    <div id="nose"></div>
                    <div id="mouth"></div>
                    <div id="body"></div>
                    <div id="button-1"></div>
                    <div id="button-2"></div>
                    <div id="foot-1"></div>
                    <div id="foot-2"></div>
            </div>
    </body>
    </html>

`main.css`:


    /* reset styles */
    * { margin: 0px; padding: 0px; }
    
    /* make the background of the page black */
    body { background: black;}
    
    /* mickey canvas */
      #canvas {
      width: 400px;
      height: 600px;
      position: relative;
      background: white;
    }
    
    /* shapes */
    /* make all divs inside of #canvas a circle */
    #canvas div{
      border-radius: 200px;
      position: absolute;
    }
    
    /* 
    adjust the top and left 
    properties of the elements
    to position them 
    */
    
    #ear-1 {
      width: 100px;
      height: 100px;
      background: black;
    
      /* try uncommenting the following code
      top: 100px;
      left: 20px;
      */
    }
    
    #ear-2 {
      width: 100px;
      height: 100px;
      background: black;
    }
    
    #head {
      width: 140px;
      height: 140px;
      background: beige;
    }
    
    #eye-1 {
      width: 25px;
      height: 25px;
      background: black;
    }
    
    #eye-2 {
      width: 25px;
      height: 25px;
      background: black;
    }
    
    #nose {
      width: 45px;
      height: 45px;
      background: black;
    }
    
    #mouth {
      width: 35px;
      height: 35px;
      background: red;
    }
    
    #body {
      width: 160px;
      height: 160px;
      background: red;
    }
    
    #button-1 {
      width: 32px;
      height: 32px;
      background: black;
    }
    
    #button-2 {
      width: 32px;
      height: 32px;
      background: black;
    }
    
    #foot-1 {
      width: 150px;
      height: 150px;
      background: yellow;
    }
    
    #foot-2 {
      width: 150px;
      height: 150px;
      background: yellow;
    }


3. Adjust the `top` and `left` properties for the `css` rules of each selector to draw Mickey. You can see my Mickey illustration here, and the CSS i used in my example here.


4. Make sure to link the files to your class homepage when you’re done.


Inspired by Damien Hirst’s Mickey series:

